1 e. The director of mineral resources or the director's designee;
2 e.f. The director of the North Dakota pipeline authority or the director's designee;
3 f.g. The director of the North Dakota transmission authority or the director's designee;
4 g.h. The director of the state energy research center or the director's designee; and
5 h.i. The president of the Bank of North Dakota or the president's designee.
6 4. The term of office for each co-chairman is two years. The term of office for the other
7 voting members is four years, and the other voting members may not serve more than
8 two consecutive terms. The terms of office for the voting members commence on July
9 first. The initial terms for the voting members of the authority must be staggered
10 following a method determined by the authority.
11 5. The authority shall meet at least semiannually. The co-chairmen shall call a meeting
12 upon written request from three voting members of the authority. Five voting members
13 is a quorum at any meeting.
14 6. The authority may not forward a recommendation to the commission unless the
15 recommendation fulfills the purposes of this chapter and is approved by a majority of
16 the voting members of the authority.
17 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 54-63.1-07 of the North Dakota Century Code is
18 amended and reenacted as follows:
19 54-63.1-07. Clean sustainable energy fund - Continuing appropriation - Line of credit -
20 Loans - Repayments.
21 1. There is created in the state treasury the clean sustainable energy fund. The fund
22 consists of all moneys transferred to the fund by the legislative assembly; loan
23 proceeds; interest upon moneys in the fund; principal and interest payments to the
24 fund; and donations, grants, and other contributions received by the commission for
25 deposit in the fund. All moneys in the fund are appropriated to the commission on a
26 continuing basis to provide grants, loans, and other financial assistance and for
27 administrative and operating costs of the authority and program pursuant to the
28 provisions under this chapter.
29 2. Any bond proceeds deposited in the fund must be used for loans or loan guarantees.
30 The Bank of North Dakota shall deposit in the fund all principal and interest paid on
31 the loans made from the fund. The Bank may use a portion of the interest paid on the
