1 outstanding loans as a servicing fee to pay for administrative costs, not to exceed
2 one-half of one percent of the amount of the interest payment. The fund must be
3 audited annually pursuant to section 6-09-29, and the cost of the audit must be paid
4 from the fund.
5 3. The Bank of North Dakota shall extend a line of credit to the industrial commission to
6 support loans or loan guarantees issued from the clean sustainable energy fund. The
7 line of credit may not exceed three hundred ninety million dollars, and the interest rate
8 associated with the line of credit must be the prevailing interest rate charged to North
9 Dakota governmental entities. The industrial commission shall repay the line of credit
10 from moneys available in the clean sustainable energy fund derived from payments
11 received on loans issued under this chapter or other sources. If the moneys available
12 from the clean sustainable energy fund on June 30, 20252029, are not sufficient to
13 repay the line of credit, the industrial commission shall request from the legislative
14 assembly a deficiency appropriation to repay the line of credit or the industrial
15 commission may repay the line of credit from other funds, as appropriated by the
16 legislative assembly.
17 4. The industrial commission may access the line of credit to the extent needed through
18 June 30, 20252029, to provide funding as authorized by the legislative assembly to
19 support loans or loan guarantees issued from the clean sustainable energy fund. Any
20 moneys borrowed from the Bank of North Dakota pursuant to this section must be
21 transferred to the clean sustainable energy fund to support loans or loan guarantees.
22 SECTION 3. TRANSFER - STRATEGIC INVESTMENT AND IMPROVEMENTS FUND -
23 CLEAN SUSTAINABLE ENERGY GRANTS AND LOANS. During the biennium beginning
24 July 1, 2025, and ending June 30, 2027, the office of management and budget shall transfer the
25 sum of $50,000,000 from the strategic investment and improvements fund to the clean
26 sustainable energy fund, as follows:
27 1. $10,000,000 for grants; and
28 2. $40,000,000 to repay a line of credit and to provide funding for loans.
